<h2>Overview</h2><p>In this tutorial, we delve into the intricate process of installing Metalcloak Overline Tube Fenders on a 2015 Jeep JK Unlimited Wrangler. This step includes not only the installation of the fenders but also highlights techniques for effectively utilizing rivet nuts (rivnuts), especially if you're tackling such a mod for the first time.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This guide will walk you through:</p><ul><li>Necessary tools and materials for the installation</li><li>Step-by-step instructions for installing the rear overline fenders</li><li>Tips for navigating challenges, including rivnut installation and modifying existing components</li></ul><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><p>Let's break this down into manageable steps to ensure a smooth installation process:</p><ol><li><strong>Preparation</strong>: Before starting, make sure you have all the necessary tools and parts. Having a rivet nut gun, a drill with the appropriate bit sizes (17/32” is crucial), and your Metalcloak fender parts readily available will set you up for success.</li><li><strong>Remove Existing Components</strong>: Start by taking off the factory flare and inner fender liner. This is straightforward and provides you with access to the necessary areas for installation.</li><li><strong>Template Alignment</strong>: Metalcloak provides templates that you’ll use to drill holes for the rivnuts. Make sure to align these carefully to avoid any misalignment during installation.</li><li><strong>Drilling and Rivnut Installation</strong>: Drill out the appropriate holes for the rivnuts using the mentioned drill bit. Use the provided self-tapping screws to secure the template in place, which simultaneously serves as pilot holes for your drill. Ensure each rivnut is installed correctly to avoid spin-out once the bolts are tightened.</li><li><strong>Coping with Challenges</strong>: If you're modifying other components, like Rock Hard 4X4 sliders, be prepared for adjustments. Sometimes, you'll need to remove other parts to continue seamlessly with the installation.</li><li><strong>Final Assembly</strong>: Once all holes are drilled and components prepared, proceed with attaching the fenders, ensuring they fit snugly and securely.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><p>Here are a few tips to make the process smoother:</p><ul><li>If you can borrow or invest in a quality rivnut gun, it will save you a lot of frustration and time.</li><li>Always check inventory before the installation day. Having the right drill bit (like the 17/32”) can be a game changer to avoid last-minute trips to the hardware store.</li><li>Use a ratcheting tool for the rivnuts where possible, as it can provide better control than a standard wrench.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Installing Metalcloak Overline Tube Fenders does require patience, especially when dealing with rivet nuts. However, with the right preparations, tools, and mindset, you can achieve a professional-looking installation that will enhance your Jeep's off-road capabilities and aesthetic appeal. Don’t hesitate to take your time, and remember that every modification is a step towards personalizing your ride.</p>

